# Collaboration & Team Standards

## Roles
- **Sheridan Richey** — Project owner and brand strategist
- **Collaborators** — As invited
- **AI assistants** — Follow [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) and `.cursor/rules/`

## Work tracking
- **GitHub Issues** are the default for tasks, bugs, and content work items
- Use issue templates and labels (see [agentic-workflows.mdc](./agentic-workflows.mdc))
- Avoid duplicating a full project tracker in markdown under `1P/` for routine work; reserve `1P/` for strategic initiative notes and decision logs

## Communication
- **GitHub** — Code, PRs, issues, and review
- **Slack (ZAG Collective)** — Community and async discussion (not a substitute for issue acceptance criteria)

## Handoffs
- Document decisions and rationale in PR descriptions or issue comments
- Link related issues and PRs
- Note known limitations and follow-ups before closing work

## Quality before merge
- Run lint and E2E locally when touching user-facing flows
- Validate ZAG alignment for content and copy changes

## Knowledge sharing
- Long-lived how-tos belong in `2A/` / `3R/` or app docs (`website/BLOG_SYSTEM_README.md`, etc.) — they **supplement** rules; they do not replace `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
